### Phase 6 Closure

- [x] Add migration 032 and fresh-schema parity for normalized respondent names,
      stable respondent identity after user-row deletion, moderator answers,
      pinned state, constrained statuses, hashed idempotency uniqueness, and
      page-scoped response migration readiness.
- [x] Add `page-interactive-response-backfill`, a resumable ID-ordered 1-500 page
      command that copies records, verifies count/key/respondent/answer/status/
      moderation/timestamp/idempotency-hash parity, preserves response row IDs on
      rerun, and emits only counts and mismatch codes.
- [x] Replace raw idempotency keys in the rollback document with SHA-256 hashes.
      Explicitly remove both raw keys and hashes from every participant, manager,
      aggregate, HTTP, audit, log, and WebSocket projection.
- [x] Gate normalized response authority on
      `PAGE_NORMALIZED_INTERACTIVE_RESPONSES` plus matched definition and response
      runs. Missing dependencies/readiness errors fail closed; migrated writes
      lock the page and section, enforce the locked section type, update normalized
      records, and refresh the compatibility projection in one transaction.
- [x] Preserve legacy response authority for non-migrated pages, including retry
      matching after a rollback document has been scrubbed to hashed idempotency
      material.
- [x] Verify normalized replay idempotency, concurrent response-limit enforcement,
      Q&A moderation, response-type race rejection, manager/participant privacy,
      raw/hash negative disclosure, and migration rerun stability in PostgreSQL.
- [x] Introduce `SectionPreset`, `preset_type`, and
      `/config/section-presets` as the preferred datasource-preset terminology;
      retain `CustomSection`, `section_type`, and `/config/custom-sections` as
      compatibility aliases because `table`/`cards`/`component` are not page
      section discriminators.
- [x] Move preset create/update/delete authorization into a required fail-closed
      service policy. Missing policy and permission-store failures never reach the
      repository.

