### Phase 7 Closure

- [x] Add migration 033 and fresh-schema parity for consecutive matched
      observations, matched-window timestamps, rollback-drill state, and
      compatibility-endpoint write telemetry. All operational fields remain
      content-free.
- [x] Add `PAGE_NORMALIZED_SECTION_READS`, defaulting off. A page reads from
      normalized definition and response rows only after matched definition and
      response migrations, zero quarantine, three consecutive zero-diff runs over
      24 hours by default, and a successful rollback projection drill.
- [x] Make cutover reads independent from `pages.content`; readiness or projection
      storage failures fail closed. Disabling the flag restores compatibility
      reads immediately without rewriting either representation.
- [x] Add bounded `page-section-cutover` audit/runbook support. It resumes by page
      ID, records a parity observation, verifies normalized -> compatibility ->
      normalized definition/response hashes, and emits only IDs, counts, statuses,
      and mismatch codes.
- [x] Count successful whole-document compatibility saves so the release-window
      preflight can detect old application clients. The preflight also requires
      all pages ready for the entire release window, empty dormant
      `page_sections`/`page_items`, and explicit operator confirmation that
      external clients and scheduled jobs have been reviewed.
- [x] Keep legacy projection writes and tables intact: repository code deliberately
      provides a non-destructive retirement preflight rather than bypassing the
      plan's real release-window and production-telemetry requirements.
- [x] Preserve the public `Page.Content` response envelope, authorization
      filtering, realtime invalidation, SEO invalidation, typed mutation, and
      frontend reconciliation contracts across read modes; no frontend storage
      branch was introduced.

### Phase 7 Verification (2026-07-18)

- [x] Focused Go service tests prove page-specific fallback/cutover behavior,
      threshold propagation, rollback-document immutability, and fail-closed
      readiness/projection errors.
- [x] Focused PostgreSQL tests prove migration rerun safety, consecutive-run
      readiness, response-migration gating, rollback drill success, normalized
      reads after deliberately damaging the compatibility document, immediate
      flag rollback, and legacy-write telemetry.
- [x] Final complete backend suite; frontend contract drift, 26 focused
      page-section tests, lint, TypeScript, and production build all pass.
- [x] Exercise the compiled retirement runbook against local PostgreSQL. It
      correctly refuses retirement while pages remain unready and the external
      dependency review has not been attested; dormant legacy tables are empty.

